The International Genetic Literacy and Attitudes Survey – Legal and
Ethical (iGLAS-LE): MASTER Data Dictionary
This is the master data dictionary for iGLAS-LE, combining all variables and response options from the Pilot and Live (V1) versions of the International Genetic Literacy and Attitudes Survey – Legal and Ethnical
education. iGLAS-LE consists of the following sections:

Appendix 1: Country Codes ...................................................................................................................................................................................................................................... 25
• Where it is not clear from the wording of the question, response options are given in italics.
• Where there is a correct response, as is the case with the Genetic Knowledge Section, the correct response is underlined.
• Variable values are given in (brackets).
If you have any questions please contact the lead researcher, Robert Chapman at r.chapman@gold.ac.uk

• My participation in this study is voluntary
• I am over 18
• I may withdraw from this research at any time and for any reason (prior to the anonymised data being shared / published)
• I may omit any questions I do not wish to answer
• All data will be treated with full confidentiality and, if published, it will not be identifiable as mine
